05840nam a22009495i 9780674067912DE-B159720190708092533.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||190708s2013    mau    fo  d z      eng d  a97806740679127 a10.4159/harvard.97806740679122doi  a(DE-B1597)177962  a(OCoLC)826855510  a(OCoLC)840444829  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  amaucUS-MA 4aBF1729.P6bA99 2013 7aHIS0370202bisacsh04a133.50945/21090242231 aAzzolini, Monica, eauthor.14aThe Duke and the Stars :bAstrology and Politics in Renaissance Milan /cMonica Azzolini. 1aCambridge, MA : bHarvard University Press, c[2013] 4cÂ©2012  a1 online resource :b17 halftones, 2 line illustrations, 3 tables  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aI Tatti Studies in Italian Renaissance History00t Frontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tIllustrations -- tIntroduction -- t1 The Science of the Stars: Learning Astrology at the University of Pavia -- t2 The Making of a Dynasty: Astrology under Bianca Maria Visconti and Francesco Sforza -- t3 Astrology Is Destiny: Galeazzo Maria Sforza and the Political Uses of Astrology -- t4 The Star-Crossed Duke: Gian Galeazzo Sforza and Medical Astrology -- t5 The Viper and the Eagle: The Rise and Fall of Astrology under Ludovico Sforza -- tEpilogue -- tAbbreviations -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tAcknowledgments -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis study is the first to examine the important political role played by astrology in Italian court culture. Reconstructing the powerful dynamics existing between astrologers and their prospective or existing patrons, The Duke and the Stars illustrates how the "predictive art" of astrology was a critical source of information for Italian Renaissance rulers, particularly in times of crisis. Astrological "intelligence" was often treated as sensitive, and astrologers and astrologer-physicians were often trusted with intimate secrets and delicate tasks that required profound knowledge not only of astrology but also of the political and personal situation of their clients. Two types of astrological predictions, medical and political, were taken into the most serious consideration. Focusing on Milan, Monica Azzolini describes the various ways in which the Sforza dukes (and Italian rulers more broadly) used astrology as a political and dynastic tool, guiding them as they contracted alliances, made political decisions, waged war, planned weddings, and navigated health crises. The Duke and the Stars explores science and medicine as studied and practiced in fifteenth-century Italy, including how astrology was taught in relation to astronomy.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aAstrology and politicsxHistory. 70(DE-601)1041522060(DE-588)4046514-7aPolitik2gnd 70(DE-601)1062933970(DE-588)4025453-7aHof2gnd 70(DE-601)10638998X0(DE-588)4003305-3aAstrologie2gnd 7aHISTORY / Renaissance.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE HISTORY, POLITICAL SCIENCE, SOCIOLOGY  2013z978311031712108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET GESCHICHTE, POLITIKWISS., SOZIOLOGIE  2013z9783110317114oZDB-23-DPS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014z978311037488908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package 2013z978311037490208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045951708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook